      {
        "title": "PM Modi extends greetings to devotees undertaking annual Amarnath Yatra in J&K",
        "summary": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi has extended his greetings to devotees undertaking the annual Amarnath Yatra in Jammu and Kashmir. In a letter written to the pilgrims, Mr Modi described the annual Amarnath Yatra as an eternal chapter in the spiritual tradition and cultural unity of the country. He said that the divine darshan of Baba […]",
        "article": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi has extended his greetings to devotees undertaking the annual Amarnath Yatra in Jammu and Kashmir. In a letter written to the pilgrims, Mr Modi described the annual Amarnath Yatra as an eternal chapter in the spiritual tradition and cultural unity of the country. He said that the divine darshan of Baba Barfani is an unforgettable and deeply auspicious experience in the lives of millions of devotees. The Prime Minister also urged devotees to take five resolutions during the pilgrimage. These include maintaining cleanliness throughout the Yatra, strictly following all safety and administrative guidelines, supporting the local economy by spending at least ten per cent of their travel expenses on local products under the Vocal for Local initiative, gifting a sapling to a sibling on Raksha Bandhan to promote the Ek Ped Maa Ke Naam campaign, and carrying the spirit of Nation First by performing their duties with honesty and contributing to the vision of a Viksit Bharat. The Prime Minister expressed confidence that the Amarnath Yatra would continue to strengthen the values of faith, cultural unity and service. He prayed for the safety and well-being of all devotees and wished that the blessings of Baba Amarnath inspire renewed energy, spiritual strength and greater dedication towards building a developed India. He also congratulated the Indian Army, CRPF, Jammu and Kashmir Police, BSF, NDRF, doctors and healthcare workers, administrative officials, sanitation workers, and every individual engaged in serving the devotees.",
        "date": "2026-07-03",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-03T05:25:21+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/pm-modi-extends-greetings-to-devotees-undertaking-annual-amarnath-yatra-in-jk/",
        "image_url": "https://newsonair.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Untitled-design-5-1.png",
        "image_credit": "Prasar Bharati / Akashvani News",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      },
      {
        "title": "PM Modi & Japanese PM Sanae Takaichi strongly condemn terrorism & violent extremism in all forms",
        "summary": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his Japanese counterpart Sanae Takaichi have unequivocally and strongly condemned terrorism and violent extremism in all its forms and manifestations, including cross-border terrorism from Pakistan. The 16th India-Japan Annual Summit Joint Statement said both leaders condemned in the strongest terms the terrorist attack in Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir, on […]",
        "article": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his Japanese counterpart Sanae Takaichi have unequivocally and strongly condemned terrorism and violent extremism in all its forms and manifestations, including cross-border terrorism from Pakistan. The 16th India-Japan Annual Summit Joint Statement said both leaders condemned in the strongest terms the terrorist attack in Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir, on 22nd April last year. The leaders also took note of the United Nations Security Council Monitoring Team Report of 29th July 2025, mentioning The Resistance Front. Akashvani correspondent reports that Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Japanese Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi also strongly condemned the terrorist attack in Delhi on 10th November last year. The two leaders called for the perpetrators, organisers and financiers of the reprehensible act to be brought to justice without delay. They also called for concerted action against all UN-listed terrorist groups and entities, including Al Qaeda, ISIS (Daesh), Lashkar-e-Tayyiba, Jaish-e-Mohammad and their proxies. The two Prime Ministers stressed the need for resolute action to eliminate terrorists&#8217; safe havens, dismantle terror financing networks and their nexus with transnational crime, and halt the cross-border movement of terrorists. Towards the shared goal of a resilient and prosperous Indo-Pacific, the two Prime Ministers reiterated their commitment to advancing cooperation among like-minded countries. They welcomed the steady progress under the Quad framework and reaffirmed their commitment to enhancing practical cooperation. They underscored the importance of collaboration across the four pillars of maritime and transnational security; economic prosperity and security, including critical minerals; critical and emerging technologies; and humanitarian assistance and emergency response. They noted that growing bilateral cooperation in these areas would further strengthen and complement Quad efforts. The leaders also highlighted the importance of cooperation with ASEAN Member States to strengthen regional resilience and promote peace, stability and prosperity.",
        "date": "2026-07-03",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-03T03:43:37+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/pm-modi-and-his-japanese-counterpart-sanae-takaichi-strongly-condemn-terrorism-violent-extremism-in-all-forms/",
        "image_url": "https://newsonair.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Untitled-design-4-1.png",
        "image_credit": "Prasar Bharati / Akashvani News",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      },
      {
        "title": "ECI seeks responses from rival factions of AITC regarding competing claims about party’s organisational elections",
        "summary": "The Election Commission of India (ECI) has sought responses from rival factions of the All India Trinamool Congress (AITC) regarding competing claims about the party’s organisational elections and authorised signatories. In a statement, the Commission said it has written separate letters to Mamata Banerjee and party leader Ritabrata Banerjee regarding the claims and counterclaims […]",
        "article": "The Election Commission of India (ECI) has sought responses from rival factions of the All India Trinamool Congress (AITC) regarding competing claims about the party’s organisational elections and authorised signatories. In a statement, the Commission said it has written separate letters to Mamata Banerjee and party leader Ritabrata Banerjee regarding the claims and counterclaims by both factions with respect to organisational elections and authorised signatories of the AITC. The Commission said both sides have been directed to submit their responses by 5.30 pm on Monday. The development comes amid a dispute within the Trinamool Congress over the party’s organisational structure and the authority to act on its behalf before the Election Commission. Such disputes are governed by the Election Symbols (Reservation and Allotment) Order, under which the Commission examines rival claims, supporting documents and submissions from the contending factions before taking a decision, where necessary. The ECI has not expressed any view on the merits of the rival claims and has sought written responses from both factions before proceeding further in the matter.",
        "date": "2026-07-03",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-03T03:42:31+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/eci-seeks-responses-from-rival-factions-of-aitc-regarding-competing-claims-about-partys-organisational-elections/",
        "image_url": "https://newsonair.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/eci-hai-yte.png",
        "image_credit": "Prasar Bharati / Akashvani News",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      }
