        "article": "In Badminton, India&#8217;s campaign ended at the Canada Open Super 300 tournament after Tanya Hemnath&#8217;s defeat in the Women&#8217;s Singles second round in Markham. Tanya lost to Japan&#8217;s Riko Gunji 21-11, 21-11 in the second round. Earlier, Hemnath beat American Disha Gupta 21-16, 21-18 in the opening round. Similarly, Commonwealth Games medallist Aakarshi Kashyap won her opening-round match against France&#8217;s Anna Tatranova but exited in the second round after losing 22-20, 17-21, 17-21 to fourth seed Beiwen Zhang of the USA. Yesterday was disappointing for India&#8217;s badminton contingent, with seven of the nine Indian shuttlers crashing out in the opening round. Former world number one Kidambi Srikanth retired due to injury in his men&#8217;s singles opener, trailing 11-10 against Malaysia&#8217;s Lee Zii Jia. Saneeth Dayanand and Sankar Subramanian also bowed out in the first round, ending India&#8217;s campaign.",
